## Antenna Interface Design

The antenna subsystem is designed to support both LTE communication and GNSS positioning features of the SIM7600E-H module. Dedicated antenna paths are implemented for the main LTE antenna, auxiliary (diversity) antenna, and GNSS antenna.

Compact U.FL connectors are used to provide reliable RF connections to external antennas. Each RF line is equipped with ESD protection devices to safeguard the system against electrostatic discharge, which is critical for externally exposed interfaces.

Capacitors are strategically placed along the RF paths for DC blocking, impedance matching, and high-frequency noise suppression. These elements help maintain signal integrity and ensure efficient RF performance.

The design also allows flexibility for tuning and optimization, making it suitable for different deployment environments and antenna configurations.

This approach results in a robust and reliable antenna system that enhances communication stability and positioning accuracy.
